    a_en: "A thread is a lightweight unit of execution enabling concurrency. Two ways to create: (1) extend Thread: `class MyThread extends Thread { public void run() {...}} new MyThread().start()`. (2) implement Runnable: `new Thread(new MyRunnable()).start()`. Prefer Runnable — it doesn't block inheritance. Always call `start()`, never `run()` directly — `start()` creates a new thread and invokes `run()` in it; calling `run()` directly executes in the current thread.",
