    a_en: "Synchronization prevents data corruption when multiple threads access shared resources. Mechanisms: `synchronized` keyword on methods or blocks. Synchronized method: entire method locked; synchronized block: specific code section locked (more efficient). Cost: performance overhead, potential deadlocks. Use when multiple threads modify shared state. \n\n**Example:** `synchronized void incrementCounter() { count++; }` ensures atomic increment. Avoid over-synchronization as it reduces parallelism.",
