    a_en: "Deadlock occurs when threads wait circularly for resources held by each other — all blocked forever. \n\n**Example:** Thread A holds Lock 1, waits for Lock 2; Thread B holds Lock 2, waits for Lock 1. Prevention: (1) lock ordering — always acquire locks in the same order. (2) timeouts — use `tryLock(timeout)`. (3) avoid nested locks. (4) use higher-level constructs (concurrent collections, ExecutorService). Detecting deadlocks requires monitoring thread states via JVisualVM or thread dumps.",
