    a: "ExecutorService quản lý thread pool, tách biệt việc submit task khỏi cơ chế thực thi. \n\n**Lợi ích:** (1) tái sử dụng thread (giảm overhead tạo thread). (2) số thread cố định (tránh OutOfMemoryError). (3) task queue (xử lý burst). (4) lifecycle management (shutdown, awaitTermination). Methods: `execute(Runnable)` (fire-and-forget), `submit(Callable)` trả Future. Tạo thread thủ công: khó quản lý, tốn kém hơn, khó test. ExecutorService là cách tiếp cận được khuyến nghị cho production code.",
    a_en: "ExecutorService manages a thread pool, decoupling task submission from execution mechanics. \n\n**Benefits:** (1) thread reuse (reduced overhead). (2) fixed thread count (prevents OutOfMemoryError). (3) task queue (handles bursts). (4) lifecycle management (shutdown, awaitTermination). Methods: `execute(Runnable)` (fire-and-forget), `submit(Callable)` returns Future. Manual threads: harder to manage, slower, less testable. ExecutorService is the recommended approach for production code.",
