    level: "intermediate",
    q: "ClassLoader là gì và có mấy loại?",
    a: "ClassLoader tải file .class vào memory lúc runtime. Ba loại: (1) Bootstrap ClassLoader: JVM built-in, tải core Java classes (`java.lang`, `java.util`). (2) Platform ClassLoader (trước Java 9 gọi là Extension ClassLoader): tải classes từ thư mục JRE extensions. (3) Application ClassLoader: tải application classpath. Hierarchy: Application → Extension → Bootstrap (parent-delegation model — con hỏi cha trước). Custom ClassLoader cho phép dynamic loading, hot-reloading. Hiểu ClassLoader quan trọng để debug JAR conflict, OSGi frameworks, application server issues.",
    a_en: "ClassLoader loads .class files into memory at runtime. Three types: (1) Bootstrap ClassLoader: JVM built-in, loads core Java classes (`java.lang`, `java.util`). (2) Platform ClassLoader (called Extension ClassLoader before Java 9): loads from JRE extensions directory. (3) Application ClassLoader: loads from application classpath. Hierarchy: Application → Extension → Bootstrap (parent-delegation — child delegates to parent first). Custom loaders enable dynamic loading and hot-reloading. Understanding ClassLoader is essential for debugging JAR conflicts and application server issues.",
    q_en: "What is a ClassLoader and what are its types?",
